esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when containers are in waiting phase with error reasons.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Container status phase=waiting, excluding normal states
// (Completed, ContainerCreating, PodInitializing).
//
// What it means:
// Container stuck in error state — unable to start or run.
//
// Common causes:
// CrashLoopBackOff, ImagePullBackOff, ErrImagePull, RunContainerError.
//
// Action needed:
// Check container status reason, review pod events, verify image availability.
TS metrics-kubernetes.container-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.container.status.phase` == "waiting"
  AND (`kubernetes.container.status.reason` IS NULL
    OR (`kubernetes.container.status.reason` != "Completed"
      AND `kubernetes.container.status.reason` != "ContainerCreating"
      AND `kubernetes.container.status.reason` != "PodInitializing"))
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.container.name`, `kubernetes.namespace`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
